text: Victor is an unincorporated community in Roberts County, in the U.S. state of South Dakota. == History == Victor was planned out in 1913, and named after Victor Township, in which it is located. A post office called Victor was created in 1913, and remained in operation until 1955. == References == Category:Unincorporated communities in the United States Category:Settlements in South Dakota
title: Victor, South Dakota
